      <hedline>
        <hl1>Offshore Wind Plan: What's the Rush?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ronald Enners letter on Long Island Power Authority chairman Richard Kessel's March 26 letter on plan to build windmills in Long Island Sound</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thanks for giving Richard Kessel's letter space in your newspaper (March 26). He apparently does not get enough press.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thanks for giving Richard Kessel's letter space in your newspaper (March 26). He apparently does not get enough press.</p>
        <p>Perhaps you didn't know that, because he is the chairman of LIPA, his statements appear almost every week in some Long Island paper. He always has something to say about the fact that Long Island has an ever-increasing energy need and dependence on fossil fuels.</p>
        <p>However, Mr. Kessel's windmill plan is purported to be part of the solution to the problem that Mr. Kessel actually helped create, by squashing the nuclear plant at Shoreham.</p>
        <p>Call Shoreham a fiasco, if you will. I call it foresight.</p>
        <p>Ronald Enners  West Babylon</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
